In [109]:
import os
In [110]:
for month in list_of_months:
    
    fig = shape.plot(column=month, cmap='RdBu', figsize=(10,10), linewidth=0.1, edgecolor='0.8', vmin=vmin, vmax=vmax,
    legend=True, legend_kwds={'shrink':0.5,'orientation':'vertical'}, norm=plt.Normalize(vmin=vmin, vmax=vmax))
    
    
    fig.axis('off')
    fig.set_title('Figures of Ward Level Crimes in London (2021)', 
              fontdict={'fontsize': '25',
                         'fontweight' : '3'})
    
    only_month= month[-2:]
    fig.annotate(only_month,
            xy=(0.07, .175), xycoords='figure fraction',
            horizontalalignment='left', verticalalignment='bottom',
            fontsize=25)
 
    filepath = os.path.join(output_path, only_month+'_crimes.jpg')
    chart = fig.get_figure()
    chart.savefig(filepath, dpi=400)
